  "prompt": "What percentage of freshers are accepted into the IIM's every year?",
  "response": "The acceptance rate for freshers into the Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) can vary from year to year and across different IIMs. Generally, the acceptance rate is low due to the highly competitive nature of the Common Admission Test (CAT) and the rigorous selection process that follows, which includes Written Ability Test (WAT), Group Discussion (GD), and Personal Interviews (PI).\n\nWhile specific percentages can fluctuate, it's estimated that a significant proportion of those accepted into various IIM programs each year are freshers, sometimes ranging from 20% to 50% across different IIMs. However, the exact percentage can vary based on factors like the specific IIM, changes in admission criteria, and the overall applicant pool in any given year.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's best to refer to official reports or announcements from the respective IIMs or data published by credible educational resources.",
